Method Detail

geocode

public void geocode(String[] values,
                    PickListener listener)
             throws IOException
Performs a geocoding operation. After calling this method, the implementation will attempt to match the specified address values against the database. If the database is on a remote web server, then the method will "block" the calling thread until a result is obtained, or an error occurs.

The result will be zero or more point features whose geometry matches the point features matching the geocode operation, together with a field that contains the "score" of the result and a field containg the matched address as a single string. The specified PickListener will be notified with one or more PickEvents containing the result.

Parameters:
values - an array of Strings that specify the address to be matched
listener - the PickListener
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if values or listener are null, or if the number of values differs from the number of input tags
IOException - if any error is encountered
See Also:
geocode(java.lang.String[], com.esri.mo2.ui.bean.PickListener)

geocode

public void geocode(String[] values,
                    PickListener listener,
                    int maxCandidates,
                    int minScore,
                    boolean pinPoint)
             throws IOException
Performs a geocoding operation with finer control over the result. By using this method, you can select the maximum number of candidates to be returned, the minimum acceptable "score", and choose to return the actual feature matched, or a synthetic point feature. In all other respects, this method operates the same as the other geocode method, which uses the defaults that are marked below.

Parameters:
maxCandidates - the maximum number of candidates, (default) 0 == no maximum set
minScore - the minimum acceptable score for a candidate to be returned, (default) 0 == no minimum score
pinPoint - (default) true == results consist of "synthetic" point locations, false == the matched features are returned
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if values or listener are null, or if the number of values differs from the number of input tags
IOException - for any error encountered
See Also:
geocode(String[],com.esri.mo2.ui.bean.PickListener)
